linoleic acid (41.4% and 37.0%, respectively). The main sterols of Berrettina pumpkin seed oil

fraction, triterpenic compounds were more abundant than aliphatic compounds (63.2% vs. 36.8%).
The obtained data are useful to evaluate pumpkin seed oil froma nutritional point of view. The oil
obtained from the seed could be used as a preservative and as a functional ingredient in different
areas, e.g., cosmetics, foods, and nutraceuticals.
